ear that funding has been cut by nearly 50%.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Stephen Lloyd (Eastbourne) (LD)       Share       I thank the hon. Gentleman for securing this important debate. The Times , which is not known for its hyperbole, stated recently in an editorial: “All politics is local, and local government is going bust”. Does he agree that the Government are culpable and must take responsibility for their funding decisions, and that it is down to them to stop local government going bust?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mike Amesbury       Share       I do. As a result of that 50% cut, services have been drastically reduced. Pressures and demands are increasing, but the Government have failed year after year to provide councils with fair and sufficient funding.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Derek Twigg (Halton) (Lab)       Share       Will my hon. Friend give way?     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Mike Amesbury       Share       I give way to my colleague and constituency neighbour.     Share          The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:     This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.     Derek Twigg       Share       I congratulate my hon. Friend on securing this important debate. He knows that Halton Borough Council, which serves our constituencies, is under extreme pressure. It is one of the smallest councils, and its budget will have been cut by nearly 60% by the end of the Parliament. Doe